helpdesk_ticket.description:
Dear PharmEasy Support Team,

This is regarding my order delivered today, which includes an Abbott
FreeStyle Libre 2 Plus CGM worth ₹5,138 that was received in a compromised
condition. When I received the package, the product box was already open
(not opened by me from the seal), and upon inspecting the contents I found
that the device itself was damaged. I placed the order and received the
delivery today itself, and I noticed this immediately upon opening the
outer package. I have already spoken with your on-call customer service
team, and they have registered Complaint ID: 22241656.

As advised by the agent, I am attaching clear images of the open box,
damaged product, and packaging for your review. The product is a critical
medical device used for continuous glucose monitoring, and any damage or
tampering directly affects both its usability and patient safety. Abbott’s
FreeStyle Libre 2 Plus is designed to provide continuous glucose readings
for effective diabetes management, and a damaged or tampered device cannot
be safely relied upon for this purpose.
<https://www.abbott.in/media-center/press-releases/abbott-launches-next-gen-freestyle-libre2-plus-with-continuous-glucose-readings-every-minute-and-optional-alarms.html>

I understand that some products are marked as non-returnable on your
platform as per your product-specific return policy. However, this is a
case of a high-value medical device being delivered with an already open
box and a damaged unit on the very day of purchase, which is fundamentally
different from a normal “change of mind” return. Your own policy highlights
the importance of intact, untampered packaging and notes that defective,
deficient or spurious products should be accepted for return or addressed
appropriately, even where return restrictions exist.
<https://pharmeasy.in/return-policy>

In view of this, I request a suitable resolution on priority in any of the
following forms:

   -

   Full refund of the amount paid for the Abbott FreeStyle Libre 2 Plus
   CGM; or
   -

   Replacement of the damaged device with a new, fully functional unit at
   no extra cost; or
   -

   Any equivalent remedy that ensures I am not forced to bear the loss for
   a damaged and open-box medical product delivered to me.

Given the urgency of using this device for glucose monitoring, I request
that this matter be treated as high priority and resolved at the earliest.
Please confirm the next steps, including whether the damaged product will
be picked up from my address and by when I can expect the
refund/replacement to be processed, in line with your stated return and
refund timelines for eligible cases.
<https://pharmeasy.in/customer-support-policy>

I have been a loyal PharmEasy customer and have trusted your platform for
essential healthcare needs. I hope this issue will be handled fairly and
promptly so that this trust is maintained. I have ordered the same product
many times previously from PharmEasy but never had an issue, it is the
first time the product damaged and opened has been received. Please help
resolve the issue.

Thank you, and I look forward to your swift response.

Best regards,
Anubhav Agrawal
9818808315
anubhav0724@gmail.com
Order ID: 654417079962681344
Complaint ID: 22241656

--

notes.body_html:
Hello Vijai,

Greetings from PharmEasy!

With regards to your order #654472220825354240-98860, as per the records, the order was assigned for a doctor consultation. Our partnered doctors tried multiple times to reach out to you for the consultation; however, they were unable to connect with you.

I am sorry to inform you that we are unable to process your order without teleconsultation, as there is no valid prescription uploaded for the order. 

We kindly request you to confirm whether the registered number or delivery number is active and accessible for the consultation so that we can arrange a callback accordingly.

Awaiting your response.

Regards,
Habiba

helpdesk_ticket.description:
To the Grievance Officer & PharmEasy Support Team,

I am writing to formally report a complete failure of service and a breach
of trust regarding my lab test order.

Order Details:
Order ID: 6219283
Date: December 1, 2025
Scheduled Slot: 08:00 AM - 09:00 AM
Amount Paid: ₹1191.96

Timeline of Harassment:
False Confirmation: My order was accepted, paid for, and confirmed for the
8-9 AM slot today.

No Show: No phlebotomist arrived during the confirmed slot.

Late Notification: I received a confirmation SMS at 4:41 PM (more than 7
hours after the slot expired).

Refusal of Home Service: The assigned phlebotomist, Mr. Amarnath Prasad,
contacted me but refused to come to my home, asking me to visit the lab
instead. I paid for Home Collection; asking me to travel to the lab is
unacceptable.

My Demand:

Under your "On Time or Free" (OTOF) policy (screenshot attached), you
guarantee that if the technician does not arrive within the slot, the test
is free (up to ₹1500 cashback).

Since you failed to deliver the service I paid for, I demand:

1- Immediate Full Refund of ₹1191.96 to my original payment source.

2- OTOF Compensation credited to my wallet immediately as per your terms.

If this refund and compensation are not processed within 24 hours, I will
be filing a formal complaint with the National Consumer Helpline (NCH).

Expectantly,

Alok Kumar

--

notes.body: Hello Mr. Alok,     Greetings from PharmEasy!   With reference to below mail & Order ID  : 6219283. Thank you for your time on the call. Pursuant to our conversation, I hope to have addressed your concerns.  We regret to inform you that the assigned phlebotomist failed to visit as per the scheduled time due to which you have faced the inconvenience & based on the seen lapses we assure you that the corrective action will be taken as per company policy to avoid such inconvenience in future.    Further as checked, the current order has been cancelled and the payment has been automatically refunded. The refund will reflect in your original payment source within 5–7 working days. We request you to place a new order using the same profile and cost. After the service order is completed, you will receive the OTOF amount in your wallet within 48–72 hours, with a validity of 60 day     Below are the usage criteria for your reference  You can pay 5% of your medicine order value with PharmEasy Credits. You can pay 50% of your Lab Test Booking value with PharmEasy Credits.    We sincerely regret the inconvenience experienced by you and shall be happy to provide you with a hassle free service in future. For any further assistance, please reach out to us through our support channels, in the App or website, listed in the 'Need Help' section.   Thank you for choosing PharmEasy. Have a great day ahead!  Regards, Reshma Kokare PharmEasy
notes.body_html:
Hello Mr. Alok,

Greetings from PharmEasy! 

With reference to below mail & Order ID  : 6219283.
Thank you for your time on the call. Pursuant to our conversation, I hope to have addressed your concerns.

We regret to inform you that the assigned phlebotomist failed to visit as per the scheduled time due to which you have faced the inconvenience & based on the seen lapses we assure you that the corrective action will be taken as per company policy to avoid such inconvenience in future.

Further as checked, the current order has been cancelled and the payment has been automatically refunded. The refund will reflect in your original payment source within 5–7 working days.
We request you to place a new order using the same profile and cost. After the service order is completed, you will receive the OTOF amount in your wallet within 48–72 hours, with a validity of 60 day

Below are the usage criteria for your reference

You can pay 5% of your medicine order value with PharmEasy Credits.
You can pay 50% of your Lab Test Booking value with PharmEasy Credits.

We sincerely regret the inconvenience experienced by you and shall be happy to provide you with a hassle free service in future.
For any further assistance, please reach out to us through our support channels, in the App or website, listed in the 'Need Help' section. 

Thank you for choosing PharmEasy. Have a great day ahead!

Regards,
Reshma Kokare
PharmEasy
